1. to know the os>>> cat /etc/os-release
		     cat /etc/redhat-release
		     cat /etc/rocky-release
2.to know host details>> hostnamectl
3.to know only hostname>>> hostname
4.to know set hostname>>> hostnamectl set-hostname hostname
5. to know kernel version>> uname-r
6. to know kernel version along with hostname>> uname-a
7. to update hostname>> su root
		        exec bash
8.to install packages>> yum install package name -y
9.to know the directory>> pwd
10.to change the directory>> cd ex:cd /opt
11.to create files>> touch filename
12.to create files along with data>> cd >filename
13.to check the data which we have entered in file>>> cat filename
14.to check append(add) the data>>> cat >>filename
15. to see long list of files>> ll---ex:1
				       2
16.to see short list of files>> 1s---ex:1 2
17.ll=ls-l
18.ls=ls-a
19.ll=ls-la (to see list with along with hiddenfiles)
20.ls -r (to reverse the files)
21.ll -a (to see hidden files)
22.to create adirectory>>> mkdir
23.to move or rename the command>>> mv sourcename filename
				   ex: mv linux-commands commands
24:to remove files>>> rm -f file name
25.to remove directory>> rm -rf filename  rmdir filename
26.to create directory  in other directory>>> mkdir destination filename
					      mkdir /root/test1
27.to create a files at a time in a directory >>> touch 1 2 3 4 
28.to create a files in series>>>hello{1..3}
29.cd ->>>command to move to previous location
30.ctrl+c>> to interrupt process
31. cd..to shift to previous directory
32.to copy files>>>> cp hello{1..3}
33.to copy the directory>>> cp -r drectoryname
34.to create subdirectories>>>> mkdir -p classr/subdirectory/directiry...
35.to shift from ending to starting directory>>>> cd ../../../
36.to shift from starting to ending directory>>> cd class5/directory/directory
37.vi-virtual interface
38.vim-virtual interface mode

